{"declarations":[{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Model/Unpacked/Operations/Compare.html#Float.Model.UnpackedFloat.beq\"><span class=\"name\">Float</span>.<span class=\"name\">Model</span>.<span class=\"name\">UnpackedFloat</span>.<span class=\"name\">beq</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">a </span><span class=\"fn\">b</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Model/Unpacked/Basic.html#Float.Model.UnpackedFloat\">UnpackedFloat</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Determines whether `a` is equal to `b` according to IEEE rules.\n\nThis is not a reflexive relation.\n","docLink":"./Init/Data/Float/Model/Unpacked/Operations/Compare.html#Float.Model.UnpackedFloat.beq","kind":"def","line":61,"name":"Float.Model.UnpackedFloat.beq","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Init/Data/Float/Model/Unpacked/Operations/Compare.lean#L61-L67"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Model/Unpacked/Operations/Compare.html#Float.Model.UnpackedFloat.lt\"><span class=\"name\">Float</span>.<span class=\"name\">Model</span>.<span class=\"name\">UnpackedFloat</span>.<span class=\"name\">lt</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">a </span><span class=\"fn\">b</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Model/Unpacked/Basic.html#Float.Model.UnpackedFloat\">UnpackedFloat</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Determines whether `a` is less than `b` according to IEEE rules.\n\nThis is not a total ordering.\n","docLink":"./Init/Data/Float/Model/Unpacked/Operations/Compare.html#Float.Model.UnpackedFloat.lt","kind":"def","line":53,"name":"Float.Model.UnpackedFloat.lt","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Init/Data/Float/Model/Unpacked/Operations/Compare.lean#L53-L59"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Model/Unpacked/Operations/Compare.html#Float.Model.UnpackedFloat.le\"><span class=\"name\">Float</span>.<span class=\"name\">Model</span>.<span class=\"name\">UnpackedFloat</span>.<span class=\"name\">le</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">a </span><span class=\"fn\">b</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Model/Unpacked/Basic.html#Float.Model.UnpackedFloat\">UnpackedFloat</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Determines whether `a` is less than or equal to `b` according to IEEE rules.\n\nThis is not a total ordering, and `≤` is not reflexive.\n","docLink":"./Init/Data/Float/Model/Unpacked/Operations/Compare.html#Float.Model.UnpackedFloat.le","kind":"def","line":45,"name":"Float.Model.UnpackedFloat.le","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Init/Data/Float/Model/Unpacked/Operations/Compare.lean#L45-L51"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Model/Unpacked/Operations/Compare.html#Float.Model.UnpackedFloat.compare\"><span class=\"name\">Float</span>.<span class=\"name\">Model</span>.<span class=\"name\">UnpackedFloat</span>.<span class=\"name\">compare</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Model/Unpacked/Basic.html#Float.Model.UnpackedFloat\">UnpackedFloat</a> → <a href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Model/Unpacked/Basic.html#Float.Model.UnpackedFloat\">UnpackedFloat</a> → <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Option\">Option</a> <a href=\"./Init/Data/Ord/Basic.html#Ordering\">Ordering</a></span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Computes the ordering between the two floats as specificed by IEEE. Returns an\n`Option Ordering` to account for the fact that `NaN` is incomparable with everything.\nAlso, positive and negative zero are equal.\n\nImportant: this operation only works correctly if the two inputs are in\ncanonical form for a common format (see the docstring for `UnpackedFloat` for details.)\n","docLink":"./Init/Data/Float/Model/Unpacked/Operations/Compare.html#Float.Model.UnpackedFloat.compare","kind":"def","line":17,"name":"Float.Model.UnpackedFloat.compare","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Init/Data/Float/Model/Unpacked/Operations/Compare.lean#L17-L43"}}],"imports":["Init.Data.Float.Model.Unpacked.Basic"],"instances":[],"name":"Init.Data.Float.Model.Unpacked.Operations.Compare"}